  "text": "CLEAN Bath time keeps you looking your best and brightest. You use bill and feet to clean yourself throughout the day A special gland on your tail produces oil that you use to your feathers. You use feet like a comb (and to scratch annoying itches). You enjoy taking baths in streams or backyard birdbaths. but there's no tub available. you wash yourself with wet leaves. You like to sunbathe and will spread your feathers to dry off and catch a few warm rays. WHY DO YOUR FEATHERS SHIMMER? Depending on your species. you may have colorful feathers that are iridescent in the sunlight. ThaB because your feathers are made of special cells that contain melanosomes. or tiny structures filled with air bubbles. When sunlight reflects off these bubbles. it creates stunning colors. It's kind of like seeing different colors in a soap bubble-but better! Please pass the shampoo.",
